widgets_values:
### 🎥 Motion-Controlled T2V Workflow  
`Use your own video to guide motion in text-to-video generation`

This workflow allows you to upload a **reference video** to guide the motion and timing of your generated output. Perfect for matching character animation to real human movement.

🛠️ How it works:

1. 📹 Upload your own **reference video** into the `Upload Video` node  
  → This could be a clip of yourself acting out a scene or performing a motion

2. 📝 Write your **text prompt** as usual  
  → Focus on character details, background, lighting, and overall style  
  → You **don’t need to describe camera motion** — it’s already embedded in the control video

3. 🔁 The model uses the uploaded video to extract motion, while applying your prompt to generate a new cinematic result

📌 This is ideal for:
- Character animation  
- Matching action or gesture timing  
- Custom motion reference for fine-tuned outputs

🧠 Tips: 
- Match the framing of your character to the composition you want in the final result

---
nodes.title: ## READ ME

widgets_values:
### 🔄 Swap DWpose with Other ControlNets  
`Use different ControlNets to change how motion or structure is guided`

You don’t have to use DWpose — you can swap in other ControlNets to get different results:

- 🌊 Depth  
- 🧱 Normal Map  
- 🖊️ Lineart  
- 🧍 OpenPose

📌 For lip sync or better facial detail:  
Use **Normal Crafter** with a **close-up video** for the best results.

Just swap the model in the ControlNet Loader and you're good to go!

---

If your setup doesn’t support torch compile, set attention mode to `sdpa` in the model loader and bypas the Torch Compile settings and adjust the base_precision to just fp16

Block swapping helps if you have lower VRAM and/or get OOM. RTX 5090 uses the current settings to prevent OOM. Raise the number till you no longer OOM (up to 40)
